Html:
Hello,

For my volleybal club we have a excel file which is protected with a password. I try to automate something for the website and therefore I want to open the Excel to import data in to a database.

Is it possible to open the Excel by PHPExcell?

(It's for me not a problem that I have the password in the code or when I load the excel file with PHPExcel, a pop-up window pops-up with the question "fill in the password")

The same identical questions from three different people in the last three days, all visible on the very first page of the discussion list, and all with a heading that indicates they're about exactly the same topic.

 

PHPExcel does not support password-protected workbooks.

Simply adding a password to a load call might be simple for a developer, but it is not simple for the library when I can't find any Microsoft documentation identifying how workbook level encryption is implemented.... makes it very difficult to know how it should be decrypted.
